<html i18n:domain="opencore"
    metal:use-macro="here/@@standard_macros/master">
    <body>
        <head>
            <title i18n:translate="about_window_title" metal:fill-slot="title">
              About - <span i18n:name="portal_title" tal:replace="view/portal_title" />
            </title>
        </head>

        <div metal:fill-slot="content">

            <div id="oc-content-main">

                <div class="oc-headingBlock">
                    <h1 i18n:translate="about_window_header">
                      About <span i18n:name="portal_title" tal:replace="view/portal_title" />
                    </h1>
                </div>
                <div i18n:translate="about_openfsm">
                    <p>
                        OpenFSM.net is a platform for participatory
                        social activism
                        <span>
                            provided by the World Social Forum.
                        </span>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Whether your group is an organisation, a
                        network, an ad hoc group preparing an activity
                        for WSF 2008, or
                        promoting a proposal for social transformation,
                        OpenFSM.net can help you work collectively.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        OpenFSM.net also helps your intercommunication
                        with many other participants and groups in the
                        ESF all working under the 
                            <a href="http://wsf2008.net/eng/node/72"
                               i18n:name="wsf2008_charter_principles_social_forums" 
                               i18n:translate="about_principles_social_forums">
                            Charter of Principles of Social Forums</a>.
                    </p>
                    <p>

                        OpenFSM is about making World Social Forum a
                        continuous process.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        With collaborative wiki pages and other tools
                        within "projects", you and your group can:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Present your cause in the project home
                                page
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Collaborate on writing documents with
                                the wiki
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>

                            <p>Publish news in the project blog</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Create and use mailing lists for the
                                project team or a for a wider
                                participant circle
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Store and share files</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>

                            <p>Share to-do lists</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Upload photos</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Contact people and other projects</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>

                            <p>
                                <span>
                                    Each project space has their own
                                    path (I.e:
                                    www.openfsm.net/ProjectName)
                                </span>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>and more...</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p align="justify">
                        <span>
                            OpenFSM.net promotes the open space
                            philosophy. By default its pages and
                            contents are public and open to every person
                            working for another Europe and a better
                            world; however each project hosted in the
                            ESFOpen tool has the option to restrict its
                            space only to its participants.
                        </span>

                    </p>

                    <p align="justify">
                        <span>
                            OpenFSM.net promotes Copyleft. The
                            contents of the Open ESF are licensed under
                            Creative Common Share Alike Licence unless a
                            specific document specifies another licence.
                        </span>
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        If you need something else or you have any
                        suggestion or question, please
                        <a tal:attributes="href string:${context/portal_url}/contact-site-admin"
                           i18n:name="let_us_know_u" 
                           i18n:translate="about_let_us_know_u">
                            <u>let us know</u>
                        </a>.
                        OpenFSM.net is using a fast evolving software
                        platform called
                        <a href="http://www.openplans.org/projects/opencore"
                           i18n:name="opencore_software" 
                           i18n:translate="about_opencore_software">
                            OpenCore
                        </a> developed by <a href="http://topp.openplans.org" i18n:name="topp_website" i18n:translate="about_topp">The Open Planning Project</a>.
                    </p>

                </div>
            </div><!-- content-main -->
            <div id="oc-content-sidebar">
                <div i18n:translate="about_let_us_know"
                    class="oc-getstarted">
                    <h2>Help!</h2>
                    <p>
                        The <a href="http://openfsm.net/projects/openfsm-website"
                               i18n:name="openfsm_website" i18n:translate="about_openfsm_website">OpenFSM Webteam</a> is here to help you. If you have a question,
                        <a tal:attributes="href string:${context/portal_url}/contact-site-admin" 
                           i18n:name="let_us_know" i18n:translate="about_let_us_know_label">
                            let us know
                        </a>.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div><!-- content-fill-slot -->
    </body>
</html>
